There is a syntax to write a technical paper, Readme.md files

Headings

* To create a heading, add one to six '#' before the heading text.
* Number of '#' determines the hierarchy level and typeface size of the heading.

Styling text 

You can emphasize the text with bold, italic, strikethrough, subscript or superscript 

	**<text>**   		# to add boldness in text
	*<text>*     		# for italic text
	~~<text>     		# strikethrough
	***<text>*** 		# bold + italic
	<sub><text></sub> 	# subscript
	<sup><text></sup>	# superscript


Quoting text

	'>' is used to quote a text.


Quoting code

	use `<code>` to quote a code.

Color midels

	Supported color models- HEX `RRGGBB`
				RGB 	rgb(R,G,B)
				HSL	hsl(H,S,L)


Links
	
* You can create inline link by wrapping link in brackets [], and then wrapping the URL in parentheses ().

		[github page](https:github.com)

Relative Links  [](file path)



Images
* display an image by adding '!' and wrapping the text in '[]' and the wrap up the image link in '()'.

		![info of image](link of the image)


Lists

* Unordered list -  use '-', '*' or '+'
* Ordered list  -   use numbers


Task lists

* To create a task list, preface list items with a hyphen and space followed by [ ]. To mark a task as complete, use [x].


Using emojis

* You can add emogy by typing :EMOJICODE:


Footnotes can created by using this brackets syntax [^1], [^2],...
	[^1]: my referance.   #Any name 
	[^2]: 2nd footmark.


Alerts

syntax->    > [!name of alert]
	    > Info of that alert.





